ol.li:
In mod periodic, dar si in cazul nerespectarii de catre parintii/reprezentantii legali ai Elevului a prevederilor legale si constractuale, categoriile de personal implicate in asigurarea starii de sanatate a elevilor in cadrul Scolii Verita vor lua urmatoarele masuri:
efectuarea de actiuni de investigare epidemiologica a elevilor suspecti de boli transmisibile sau contacti;
depistarea, izolarea si declararea copiilor suspecti de boli transmisibile;
anuntarea familiei/a reprezentantilor legali pentru preluarea elevului in cauza, respectiv anuntarea medicului specialist/a medicului de familie/ a Serviciului Unic de Urgenta; parintele/tutorele sau o persoana desemnata de acesta are obligatia de a se prezenta la scoala in cel mai scurt timp posibil pentru preluarea elevului, fiind raspunzator de evolutia starii de sanatate a acestuia;
refuzul de a permite reintrarea in colectivitate a elevilor pentru care parintii/reprezentantii legali nu prezinta avizul epidemiologic eliberat de medicul de familie dupa diagnosticarea cu o boala contagioasa sau dupa o perioada de absenta din colectivitate de cel putin 3 zile consecutive.

Periodically, as well as in the case of non-compliance by the Student’s parents/legal representatives with the legal and contractual provisions, the personnel categories involved in protecting the health of the Verita School students will take the following measures:
conducting epidemiological investigations on the students suspected of transmissible diseases or their contacts;
detecting, isolating and declaring the children suspected of transmissible diseases;
announcing the family/legal representatives to pick up the child or informing the specialist/family doctor/ calling the Emergency Services Number; the parent/tutor/person delegated by the latter must come to school within the shortest time possible in order to pick up the student and will be responsible for the evolution of his/her state of health;
refusing to allow re-entry into the school setting of students whose parents/legal representatives do not provide the epidemiological certificate issued by the family doctor after having been diagnosed with a contagious disease or after an absence period from the school setting of minimum 3 consecutive days.

